## 1. Prerequisites

Before starting, make sure you have:

- [ ] **A Phantom Wallet** (browser extension) with at least **2–3 SOL** for deployment fees.
- [ ] **Your NFT artwork files** ready (77 images, already generated in `/art/metadata/`).
- [ ] **Your NFT metadata JSON files** ready (77 JSON files, already generated in `/art/metadata/`).
- [ ] **A pinned IPFS CID** for the artwork folder (you should have this from uploading to Pinata or nft.storage).
- [ ] **Access to the following browser tools:**
  - [Solana Playground](https://beta.solpg.io) — for deploying the smart contract
  - [SPL Token UI](https://spl-token-ui.com) or [Token Creator on Smithii](https://smithii.io/token-creator) — for creating SPL tokens
  - [Metaplex Umi / Sugar CLI](https://docs.metaplex.com) or [Crossmint](https://crossmint.com) or [Underdog Protocol](https://underdogprotocol.com) — for NFT collection minting

---

## 2. Create the SSS10i Reward Token (The Free Way)

Instead of paying expensive fees on UIs like Smithii, we will use **Solana Playground's Client** feature to create your token with metadata for free (you only pay the ~0.015 SOL standard network rent).

### Step 2.1: Upload Token Image & Metadata

Before running the script, your token needs a JSON metadata file hosted online.

1. Go to [https://app.pinata.cloud](https://app.pinata.cloud) (or any IPFS provider).
2. Upload `sss10i.jpg` (your logo). Get the image CID URL.
3. Create a file called `sss10i_metadata.json` locally:

```json
{
  "name": "SSS10i",
  "symbol": "SSS10I",
  "description": "SSS10i is the single reward token for the Facility Sieben DeFi protocol.",
  "image": "https://gateway.pinata.cloud/ipfs/YOUR_IMAGE_CID/sss10i.jpg",
  "external_url": "https://sss10i.com"
}
```

4. Upload `sss10i_metadata.json` to Pinata.
5. **WRITE DOWN the JSON Metadata URL** (e.g. `https://gateway.pinata.cloud/ipfs/YOUR_JSON_CID`).

### Step 2.2: Run the SolPG Creation Script

1. Go to [https://beta.solpg.io](https://beta.solpg.io).
2. Ensure your wallet is connected and you are on **Mainnet-beta** in the bottom-left corner.
3. In the left sidebar, click the **Client** icon (it looks like a terminal/code file) or just create a file named `client.ts` in your `client/` folder.
4. Paste the following script into `client.ts`:

```typescript
import {
  createMint,
  getOrCreateAssociatedTokenAccount,
  mintTo,
  setAuthority,
  AuthorityType,
} from "@solana/spl-token";
import {
  PublicKey,
  Transaction,
  sendAndConfirmTransaction,
} from "@solana/web3.js";
import { createCreateMetadataAccountV3Instruction } from "@metaplex-foundation/mpl-token-metadata";

// --- CONFIGURATION ---
const MINT_DECIMALS = 9;
const MINT_SUPPLY = 77 * 10 ** MINT_DECIMALS; // 77 SSS10i tokens
const TOKEN_NAME = "SSS10i";
const TOKEN_SYMBOL = "SSS10I";
const TOKEN_URI = "YOUR_JSON_METADATA_URL_HERE"; // Paste your Pinata JSON link here!
// ---------------------

async function main() {
  console.log("🚀 Creating your SPL Token...");

  // 1. Create Mint
  const mint = await createMint(
    pg.connection,
    pg.wallet.keypair,
    pg.wallet.publicKey, // mint authority
    pg.wallet.publicKey, // freeze authority
    MINT_DECIMALS,
  );
  console.log("✅ Mint Address:", mint.toBase58());

  // 2. Create Your Token Account
  const tokenAccount = await getOrCreateAssociatedTokenAccount(
    pg.connection,
    pg.wallet.keypair,
    mint,
    pg.wallet.publicKey,
  );

  // 3. Mint the Total Supply to your wallet
  await mintTo(
    pg.connection,
    pg.wallet.keypair,
    mint,
    tokenAccount.address,
    pg.wallet.publicKey,
    MINT_SUPPLY,
  );
  console.log(
    `✅ Minted ${MINT_SUPPLY / 10 ** MINT_DECIMALS} tokens to your wallet.`,
  );

  // 4. Attach Metaplex Metadata
  const TOKEN_METADATA_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(
    "metaqbxxUerdq28cj1RbAWkYQm3ybzjb6a8bt518x1s",
  );
  const [metadataPDA] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(
    [
      Buffer.from("metadata"),
      TOKEN_METADATA_PROGRAM_ID.toBuffer(),
      mint.toBuffer(),
    ],
    TOKEN_METADATA_PROGRAM_ID,
  );

  const metadataInstruction = createCreateMetadataAccountV3Instruction(
    {
      metadata: metadataPDA,
      mint: mint,
      mintAuthority: pg.wallet.publicKey,
      payer: pg.wallet.publicKey,
      updateAuthority: pg.wallet.publicKey,
    },
    {
      createMetadataAccountArgsV3: {
        data: {
          name: TOKEN_NAME,
          symbol: TOKEN_SYMBOL,
          uri: TOKEN_URI,
          sellerFeeBasisPoints: 0,
          creators: null,
          collection: null,
          uses: null,
        },
        isMutable: true,
        collectionDetails: null,
      },
    },
  );

  const tx = new Transaction().add(metadataInstruction);
  await sendAndConfirmTransaction(pg.connection, tx, [pg.wallet.keypair]);
  console.log("✅ Metadata attached!");

  // 5. Disable Minting Forever (Enforces the 77 fixed supply cap)
  await setAuthority(
    pg.connection,
    pg.wallet.keypair,
    mint,
    pg.wallet.publicKey,
    AuthorityType.MintTokens,
    null,
  );
  console.log("🔒 Minting disabled. Supply is permanently fixed.");
  console.log("--------------");
  console.log("🎉 SUCCESS! Save your Mint Address:", mint.toBase58());
}

main();
```

5. **CRITICAL:** Update `YOUR_JSON_METADATA_URL_HERE` in the code with the link you got from Pinata.
6. Click the **Run** button at the top of the editor (or type `run` in the playground terminal).
7. Approve the transactions.
8. The console will output your new **Mint Address**. **WRITE THIS DOWN as your `SSS10i_MINT`.**

> [!NOTE]
> SolPG automatically installs packages like `@solana/spl-token` in their browser environment when you hit Run. It just works!

---

## 3. CARDANO Community Token (Already Live)

The $CARDANO community token is **already live on Mainnet**. You do NOT need to create a new token.

Because it is already deployed, simply use its live Mainnet Mint Address:

**`2HE1yvnVitiBEzU1fud7kPsGv89eP7TBwSd8D3tPpump`**

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Use this exact address for `CARDANO_MINT` in your frontend and smart contract LP creations.

